According to a State House press release today, the ceremony which was presided over by the Prime Minister Kassim Majaliwa and Deputy Minister for Foreign Affairs, East African, Regional and International Co-operation…. After the swearing ceremony, Ambassador Nassoro promised that he would focus more on economic diplomacy, as a new strategy that is being used by many countries in the world. On his side, Ambassador Kaniki thanked President Magufuli for elevating him into the post and promised to cement good existing relationship between Tanzania and Zambia that was established by the Founding fathers Mwalimu Nyerere and Dr Keneth Kaunda.  He further said that he would put into practice the government’s desire to develop Tanzania Zambia Railway Authority (TAZARA) which is an economic backbone between the two countries.